
# 2026-03-03 02:21:26.537436
+Build a complete biblical studies citation formatter web app called ScholaCite. Here are the full requirements:
+
+## App: ScholaCite — Biblical Studies Citation Formatter
+
+### What it does
+Users upload a PDF or Word document (a journal article or book chapter). The app extracts the bibliographic metadata and formats it as a proper citation in the chosen journal style.
+
+### Citation styles to support
+1. SBL/JBL — SBL Handbook of Style 2nd ed. + Chicago 17th. Footnote style only.
+2. JSOT — Author-date OR footnote (flexible).
+3. JSNT — SAGE Harvard (author-date system).
+4. Generic SBL — Standard SBL for books, journal articles, essays in collections.
+
+### Freemium model
+- 1 free conversion per user per month tracked by localStorage
+- After 1st use show: 'You have used your free conversion this month. Upgrade for unlimited — $5/month.'
+- Paywall placeholder button (no real Stripe yet)
+
+### Tech stack
+- Pure HTML + CSS + vanilla JS frontend (index.html + style.css)
+- Python FastAPI backend (main.py)
+- PyMuPDF (fitz) for PDF extraction
+- python-docx for DOCX extraction
+- Claude API (anthropic library, model: claude-3-5-haiku-20241022) to extract metadata and format citation
+- requirements.txt
+- README.md with setup instructions
+
+### UI Design
+- Clean academic feel. White background, serif font Georgia, dark navy #1a2744 accents
+- Title: ScholaCite with tagline Biblical Studies Citation Formatter
+- Step 1: Upload file drag-and-drop zone accepting .pdf and .docx
+- Step 2: Choose citation style dropdown
+- Step 3: Format Citation button
+- Output: formatted citation in copyable text box with Copy button
+- Usage counter: X of 1 free conversions used this month
+- Mobile responsive
+
+### API
+- Backend runs on port 8000 with CORS enabled
+- POST /format-citation accepts JSON: {file_base64, filename, style}
+- Returns JSON: {citation, metadata}
+- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from environment variable
+- Max file size 10MB
+- Handle errors gracefully
+
+Create all files: index.html, style.css, main.py, requirements.txt, README.md

